  },
  "final_decision": "我深吸一口气，看着那份方案，然后抬眼看向对方，语气平稳而有分寸：'大方向我理解，也接受。过渡期由我来盯，这个我承诺。'（停顿，翻开方案）'不过在确认执行细节之前，我需要把几个节点的具体风险说清楚——不是能不能改的问题，是这样推进的话，哪几个环节会先出问题，我们得提前想好怎么接。这样我才能真正把过渡盯死。'我用笔点了点方案上的几个关键位置，继续说：'这些地方涉及到现有的数据流和人员协作，如果不提前梳理，可能会卡在执行层。你要的节奏我保，但我需要你信任我的判断——告诉我，这份方案是基于对现流程的哪些具体观察做出来的，这样我才能确定新流程有没有覆盖到那些问题。'",
    "final_decision_en": "I take a breath, look at the plan, then meet their eyes with a measured tone: 'I understand the direction and accept it. I commit to managing the transition period.' (Pause, open the document) 'But before confirming execution details, I need to clarify the specific risks at a few nodes—not whether we can change, but which steps will hit problems first, so we can prepare. That's how I can actually lock down the transition.' I point my pen at several key positions on the plan: 'These involve current data flows and team coordination. Without advance planning, execution could stall. I'll hit your timeline, but I need you to trust my judgment—tell me what specific observations of the current process this plan is based on, so I can confirm the new process covers those issues.'"
